message.content:
Black-footed Albatross:  
-Size and Shape: Large seabird, wingspan ~6.5 ft, long, narrow wings, bulky body  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Uniform dark sooty brown to blackish overall  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Dark brown head, no distinct facial markings, slightly lighter around base of bill  
-Wing Pattern: Dark brown upper and underwings with subtle lighter edging on flight feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, rounded, uniformly dark brown to black tail  
-Beak: Large, thick, dark gray to black, slightly hooked at tip  
-Legs and Feet: Black webbed feet and legs, sturdy appearance

Laysan Albatross:
-Size and Shape: Large, robust body with long, broad wings
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Pale gray to white body with darker gray upper wings and back
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White head with a distinct dark smudge around the eyes extending to the nape
-Wing Pattern: Dark gray upper wing surfaces contrasting with paler underwings
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium length, rounded tail, pale gray
-Beak: Large, thick, pale grayish with a curved hooked tip
-Legs and Feet: Pink to pale flesh-colored, webbed feet

Sooty Albatross:  
-Size and Shape: Large, bulky body with broad, long wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Dark sooty brown to nearly black all over, lighter grayish underwing  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Uniform dark head with faint lighter patch behind eye sometimes visible  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform dark upperwings, slightly paler underwings with subtle mottling  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, wedge-shaped, dark brown to black  
-Beak: Large, thick, dark gray to black with pronounced hook at tip  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black, webbed feet

Groove-billed Ani:  
-Size and Shape: Medium size, elongated body, long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Uniform glossy black throughout  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Smooth black head, no distinct eye ring or markings  
-Wing Pattern: Entirely black wings with slight gloss, no contrasting patches  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, rounded tail, solid black  
-Beak: Large, thick, black with distinctive deep longitudinal grooves on upper mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Black legs and feet, slender

Crested Auklet:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact seabird with a rounded body and short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Uniform smoky gray to slate gray upperparts; paler gray underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Prominent forward-curving crest of orange feathers on forehead; pale gray face; red eye with subtle white eyering  
-Wing Pattern: Dark gray wings with lighter gray edging on secondary feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, slightly rounded, dark gray tail  
-Beak: Bright orange-red, short and stout with a slight downward curve  
-Legs and Feet: Orange to reddish-orange legs and feet, webbed

Least Auklet:  
-Size and Shape: Very small, compact body with short wings and tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Pale gray upperparts, white underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White face with a faint gray crown and small black eye; prominent white plumes extending backward from the eye  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform pale gray on upper wings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square, gray tail  
-Beak: Short, black, slightly conical  
-Legs and Feet: Black, webbed feet

Parakeet Auklet:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact seabird with short neck and rounded body  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Mostly slate gray to black back and wings; white breast and belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Prominent white plumes or “whiskers” extending backward from the base of the bill; black crown and nape  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform dark gray to black upper wings with no distinct markings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square, black tail  
-Beak: Short, thick, bright orange bill with a distinct red spot near the tip; swollen base of the bill  
-Legs and Feet: Bright orange legs and webbed feet

Rhinoceros Auklet:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized auk, chunky body, short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Dark slate gray to black upperparts, white underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Dark head with a faint pale line from eye to nape, orange-yellow facial skin at base of bill during breeding  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform dark gray to black, no distinct markings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square tail, dark gray to black  
-Beak: Large, thick, orange-yellow with a prominent horn-like extension on upper mandible (rhinoceros-like) during breeding season  
-Legs and Feet: Orange to reddish-orange, webbed feet

Brewer Blackbird:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized passerine, slender body, relatively long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Males glossy iridescent black all over; females dark brown overall with lighter brown underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Males with iridescent purple-green sheen on head; females plain brown without sheen  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform black in males; females brown with slightly paler wing edges  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, slightly rounded tail, black in males, dark brown in females  
-Beak: Straight, pointed, black  
-Legs and Feet: Black legs and feet, slender

Red-winged Blackbird:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slim body with long legs and pointed wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Glossy black body; bright red shoulder patches bordered with yellow on males  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Completely black head with no distinct markings  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with conspicuous red and yellow epaulets visible in males  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, slightly rounded black tail  
-Beak: Straight, conical, black beak  
-Legs and Feet: Strong, black legs and feet with long toes for perching

Rusty Blackbird:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slim build with long legs and slightly rounded tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Mottled rusty brown edges on otherwise black plumage; rusty-scaled appearance especially on breast and flanks during non-breeding season  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Glossy dark head with subtle rusty edging on feathers; pale yellow eye  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform dark wings with faint rusty fringes on feathers in non-breeding plumage  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium length, slightly rounded tail; black with faint rusty feather edges  
-Beak: Straight, slender, dark gray to black, slightly decurved tip  
-Legs and Feet: Long, slender, dark gray to black legs and feet

Yellow-headed Blackbird:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky blackbird with a robust body and straight posture  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Glossy black body with bright yellow head and chest; black wings and tail  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Bright yellow head and throat, extending down to upper chest; no distinct eye ring or cheek patch  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with a prominent white wing bar visible in flight and at rest  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, square-edged black tail  
-Beak: Conical, pointed, black beak  
-Legs and Feet: Strong, black legs and feet

Bobolink:  
-Size and Shape: Small to medium-sized, stocky with short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Males have black underparts and back, buffy yellow rump; females and non-breeding males buffy-streaked brown and cream  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Males have pale yellow crown and nape, black face and throat; females have streaked brown head without bold markings  
-Wing Pattern: Males show white wing patches contrasting with black wings; females have streaked brown wings without distinct white patches  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, rounded tail black in males with white edges; streaked brown in females  
-Beak: Short, conical, pale pink to gray  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish or flesh-colored legs and feet

Indigo Bunting:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body; short tail; conical bill  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Vibrant cobalt blue all over in males; females brown with faint blue tinges  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Uniform bright blue crown and face (males); females have streaked brown head  
-Wing Pattern: Blue wings with subtle darker edges in males; plain brown in females  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, slightly notched tail; blue in males, brown in females  
-Beak: Short, thick, pale gray conical beak  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black legs and feet

Lazuli Bunting:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact songbird with short, conical bill  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright sky blue upperparts; white belly and breast; rusty orange flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Blue crown and nape; no distinct eye ring; slight white throat patch  
-Wing Pattern: Blue wings with two faint white wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, blue tail with notched tip  
-Beak: Short, stout, pale gray conical beak  
-Legs and Feet: Small, dark gray legs and feet

Painted Bunting:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact songbird with short tail and stout body  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Males have bright green back, red belly, blue head, and yellowish-green rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Vivid royal blue crown and nape, red eye patch continuous with red breast  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with subtle green edging, no strong bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, slightly notched tail, dark with greenish tones  
-Beak: Short, thick, conical, pale horn-colored  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to light gray legs and feet

Cardinal:
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky body with a prominent crest on head
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright red overall in males; females are pale brown with reddish tinges on wings, tail, and crest
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Distinct pointed crest; black mask around face extending from beak to throat (males)
-Wing Pattern: Solid red wings in males; females show subtle reddish wing edges
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, squared tail, bright red in males, muted reddish in females
-Beak: Thick, short, conical, bright orange-red beak
-Legs and Feet: Medium-length legs and feet, grayish to pinkish tone

Spotted Catbird:
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slim body with long tail
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-green back; grayish to olive breast and belly with prominent white spotting on flanks and underparts
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Gray crown and nape; lacking distinct eye rings or facial stripes
-Wing Pattern: Olive-green wings with faint, subtle spotting
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, rounded tail, olive-green with faint barring
-Beak: Medium length, slightly curved, dark gray to black
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black legs and feet

Gray Catbird:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slim, thrush-like body; medium-length tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Uniform slate gray overall; paler underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Slate gray crown and nape, no distinct eye ring or markings  
-Wing Pattern: Plain slate gray wings, no prominent wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, straight tail with a rusty chestnut patch visible only in flight  
-Beak: Straight, slender, dark gray to black beak  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black legs and feet

Yellow-breasted Chat:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, chunky songbird with long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-green back, bright yellow breast and belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White “spectacles” around bright yellow eyes, white throat, olive nape  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with two white wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long tail, olive-green with faint white edges  
-Beak: Thick, slightly curved, pale gray to pinkish  
-Legs and Feet: Pale gray to greenish legs and feet

Eastern Towhee:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized sparrow, robust body, long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Black upperparts (male) or brown upperparts (female), white belly, rich rufous flanks, white undertail coverts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black head and throat (male), brown head and throat (female), no distinct eye ring  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with two conspicuous white wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, rounded tail predominantly black with outer tail feathers white-edged  
-Beak: Short, thick, conical, dark gray to black  
-Legs and Feet: Stout, pinkish to dark gray legs and feet

Chuck-will's-widow:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized nightjar, elongated body, broad rounded wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Mottled brown, black, buff with complex cryptic pattern on back and wings; paler belly with fine streaks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Cryptic mottling on crown and nape; buffy supercilium faint but present; dark eye with subtle pale eye ring  
-Wing Pattern: Broad wings with intricate bars and spots in brown, buff, black  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, rounded tail with broad dark bands and narrow pale bands  
-Beak: Short, broad, slightly curved, dark upper mandible with lighter lower mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Short legs, grayish or dull brown feet, small toes

Brandt Cormorant:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized cormorant, streamlined body, relatively long neck  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Iridescent dark blue-black back and wings, paler grayish to whitish underparts during breeding season  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Small white throat patch during breeding season, bright blue throat patch (gular skin), greenish eyes  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform dark, glossy upperwing with no visible barring or spots  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, stiff, dark tail feathers  
-Beak: Medium-length, hooked tip, pale yellow to grayish  
-Legs and Feet: Short, black legs with webbed feet

Red-faced Cormorant:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-large, bulky body with relatively short neck  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Glossy black body with iridescent greenish-blue sheen on back and wings  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Prominent bright red facial skin around eyes extending to cheek and base of bill  
-Wing Pattern: Uniformly dark with shiny iridescence, no distinct wing bars or spots  
-Tail Shape and Color: Stiff, moderately long, black tail feathers  
-Beak: Thick, hooked, pale grayish with slight yellow at base  
-Legs and Feet: Black legs and webbed feet

Pelagic Cormorant:  
-Size and Shape: Small, slender body with narrow wings and long neck  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Glossy black with subtle greenish or bluish sheen; white patch on flanks in breeding adults  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black head with slender neck; red eyes; no prominent facial markings  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform glossy black without contrasting patterns  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, narrow, and pointed tail; black  
-Beak: Thin, long, dark gray with slight downward hook at tip  
-Legs and Feet: Short black legs; webbed black feet

Bronzed Cowbird:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, chunky body with relatively short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Glossy black with iridescent bronze-green sheen on back and wings  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Glossy black head, no distinct markings, slight iridescence extending into neck  
-Wing Pattern: Uniformly glossy black with bronze-green iridescence, no wing bars or spots  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square-shaped tail, glossy black  
-Beak: Thick, stout, conical, black  
-Legs and Feet: Black, sturdy legs and feet

Shiny Cowbird:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, compact body with relatively short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Glossy black overall with slight iridescent sheen  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Uniform glossy black crown and face, no distinct markings  
-Wing Pattern: Uniformly glossy black, no distinct wing bars or spots  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium length, straight, glossy black  
-Beak: Short, stout, pale bluish-gray to horn-colored  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black, slender legs

Brown Creeper:  
-Size and Shape: Small, slender, curved climbing body; stiff tail for support  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Mottled brown and white back with rusty-buff underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Brown crown with fine buff streaks; distinct white supercilium; dark eye line  
-Wing Pattern: Brown wings with faint buff wing bars and mottling  
-Tail Shape and Color: Narrow, stiff, brown tail with white edges  
-Beak: Thin, slender, long, distinctly downcurved, pale brown to gray  
-Legs and Feet: Strong, pale gray to brown legs and feet adapted for vertical climbing

American Crow:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-large, robust body; long legs; relatively long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Uniform glossy black all over  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Glossy black crown and nape, no distinct markings; dark eyes blending with plumage  
-Wing Pattern: Solid black wings with slightly rounded tips, no contrasting patterns  
-Tail Shape and Color: Fan-shaped, long, solid black tail  
-Beak: Large, thick, straight black beak with slight curve at tip  
-Legs and Feet: Long, sturdy, black legs and feet

Fish Crow:
-Size and Shape: Small to medium-sized crow, compact body, slightly shorter tail than American Crow
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Glossy black throughout with slight greenish or purplish iridescence
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Uniform black head, no distinct markings, smooth feathering around eyes
-Wing Pattern: Uniform black wings, no white or pale patches
-Tail Shape and Color: Slightly rounded black tail, shorter than American Crow
-Beak: Shorter, slender, black beak with slight curve at tip
-Legs and Feet: Black legs and feet, relatively short and strong

Black-billed Cuckoo:  
- Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slender body with long tail and relatively short wings  
- Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Warm brown upperparts; white to pale buff underparts; slight rufous tinge on flanks  
- Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Brown crown and nape; faint dark eye line; pale eyering subtle  
- Wing Pattern: Rufous patch visible on underwing coverts during flight; brown upper wings  
- Tail Shape and Color: Long, graduated tail with white spots on underside of blackish tail feathers  
- Beak: Thin, slightly curved, entirely black bill  
- Legs and Feet: Pale grayish legs and feet, relatively short

Mangrove Cuckoo:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slender body with long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-brown back, white throat and breast, buffy belly, pale flanks, rusty or cinnamon rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Dark brown crown, bold black eyeline extending from bill through eye, creamy white supercilium above eye, pale cheek patch  
-Wing Pattern: Olive-brown wings with rufous patches visible in flight  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long tail with dark upper tail coverts and wide white tips on outer tail feathers  
-Beak: Stout, slightly curved blackish bill with pale base  
-Legs and Feet: Greenish-gray legs and feet

Yellow-billed Cuckoo:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slender body; long tail and wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Warm brown back and wings; white to pale buff underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Brown crown; faint white eye-ring; plain face; no bold markings  
-Wing Pattern: Wings broad with primary feathers showing rufous/cinnamon tones underneath  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, graduated tail with white spots on black outer tail feathers; underside of tail white with dark spots  
-Beak: Long, slender, slightly curved; bright yellow lower mandible contrasting with dark upper mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Grayish legs and feet, relatively weak-looking for perching

Gray crowned Rosy Finch:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, robust finch with stout body and short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Mottled gray and brown back; pinkish rosy wash on breast, belly, and flank; lighter gray rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Distinct pale gray crown with golden yellow patch on top; dark face mask including cheek and eye area; gray nape  
-Wing Pattern: Dark brown wings with some light gray edging on feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, slightly notched tail; dark brown to black with lighter outer feathers  
-Beak: Short, thick, conical beak; pale horn to grayish color  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black legs and feet

Purple Finch:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-small songbird, robust body, slightly notched tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Males - raspberry red forehead, breast, and rump; brown streaked back and flanks; Females - brown and white streaked throughout with no red  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Males - red crown and nape with subtle facial stripe; Females - brown crown with fine streaks and pale eyebrow stripe  
-Wing Pattern: Brown wings with two pale wing bars in females; males have faint wing bars indistinct due to red wash  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium length, slightly notched tail, brown with subtle reddish wash in males  
-Beak: Short, conical, pale horn-colored beak  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to light brown legs and feet

Northern Flicker:
-Size and Shape: Medium woodpecker size, rounded head, slightly curved long bill
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Brown barred back, buff to tan breast with black spots, yellow or red shafted underwings and undertail
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Red crescent on nape, black malar stripe (men) or none (women), white or light face with dark eye ring
-Wing Pattern: Prominent black bars on brown upper wings, bright yellow or red feather shafts visible in flight
-Tail Shape and Color: Stiff tail with black barring, white rump patch visible in flight
-Beak: Long, slightly curved, grayish to brownish
-Legs and Feet: Gray to blue-gray, strong feet for clinging to tree trunks

Acadian Flycatcher:  
-Size and Shape: Small to medium, compact body with a relatively short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-green back and wings; pale yellowish-white breast and belly; slightly lighter flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Grayish crown; distinct white eye-ring forming a broken ring; pale gray cheeks  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with two faint wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, rounded tail, olive-green like back  
-Beak: Short, broad, dark upper mandible with pale lower mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black legs and feet

Great Crested Flycatcher:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky with a slightly rounded head and long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-brown back, bright yellow belly, rusty brown tail with rufous undertail coverts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Gray crown, rufous crest sides, bold white throat, slight eye ring  
-Wing Pattern: Olive-brown wings with faint rufous edging on secondary feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, squared tail, bright rusty orange on underside and tips  
-Beak: Short, broad, dark with pale base on lower mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black, sturdy feet and legs

Least Flycatcher:
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body with short tail and rounded head  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-gray upperparts; white underparts with light gray flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Distinct white eye ring; dark gray crown; subtle pale throat patch  
-Wing Pattern: Two bold white wing bars on dark gray wings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square tail with dark gray coloration  
-Beak: Small, thin, dark upper mandible with paler lower mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black legs and feet

Olive-sided Flycatcher:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky, large-headed flycatcher with a short neck and a short, stout bill  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-gray upperparts; white to pale gray underparts with pronounced, dark gray to black "vest" or patch on upper chest and sides of breast  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Dark crown with a slight crest; pale supercilium (eyebrow stripe); dark eye line; unmarked pale cheeks and nape  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with pale wing bars (usually two thin, white wing bars on folded wing)  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, squared to slightly rounded tail; dark brown to blackish  
-Beak: Short, broad at base, dark upper mandible with paler lower mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Dark legs and feet

Scissor-tailed Flycatcher:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slender, with exceptionally long, deeply forked tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Pale gray back, white underparts with pinkish wash on flanks and belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Light gray crown, white face with thin dark line through eye, subtle cheek patch  
-Wing Pattern: Dark gray to black outer wings with white wing linings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Very long, black scissor-shaped tail feathers with white edges  
-Beak: Short, broad, slightly hooked, dark gray to black  
-Legs and Feet: Thin, dark gray legs and feet

Vermilion Flycatcher:
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body with a medium-length tail and rounded wings
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Males bright vermilion red on breast and belly; back and wings dark brown to black; females duller with pale yellowish underparts and brownish upperparts
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Males have solid red crown; females have grayish crown with faint streaks; small white eye ring or crescent usually present
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with subtle rufous edges in males; plain brown wings in females
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, slightly notched tail; dark brown to black with rufous outer edges in males
-Beak: Short, broad, flat, black with slightly hooked tip
-Legs and Feet: Blackish, slender legs and feet

Yellow-bellied Flycatcher:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact flycatcher with short neck and medium-length tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-green upperparts, pale yellow underparts with brighter yellow on belly and flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Olive crown with faint streaks, prominent white or pale yellowish eye ring, grayish cheeks  
-Wing Pattern: Two pale wing bars contrasting with darker olive wings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, slightly rounded tail, olive-green matching back  
-Beak: Short, broad, dark upper mandible with paler lower mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Dark legs, relatively short and slender

Frigatebird:  
-Size and Shape: Very large, slender body; extremely long, narrow wings; deeply forked tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Mostly black or black with slight iridescence; males have distinctive red throat pouch  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Long, slender neck; bare throat patch (red in males during breeding); slight crest on nape  
-Wing Pattern: Uniformly black, narrow wings with long primary feathers giving a pointed appearance  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, deeply forked tail, solid black  
-Beak: Long, hooked, pale gray to light blue with darker tip  
-Legs and Feet: Short legs, dark-colored feet with webbing

Northern Fulmar:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky seabird with thick neck and robust body  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Pale gray to white body with darker gray on back and upper wings  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White head often with subtle gray smudging on crown and nape, dark eyes without distinct eye ring  
-Wing Pattern: Broad wings with darker gray upper surfaces contrasting with pale underwings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, squared tail, matching gray tone of back  
-Beak: Stout, pale yellow to grayish with narrow tubular nostrils on top  
-Legs and Feet: Pink to pale gray, webbed feet

Gadwall:
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized dabbling duck, slim profile, rounded head
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Mottled gray-brown body, black rear flanks and rump
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Plain gray-brown head, no distinct eye stripe or markings
-Wing Pattern: Bold white speculum patch contrasting with gray wings, black secondary feathers
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, slightly pointed tail, blackish
-Beak: Dark gray, relatively narrow and slightly flattened
-Legs and Feet: Orange to yellow-orange legs and feet, moderately webbed

American Goldfinch:
-Size and Shape: Small, stocky finch with short, conical shape
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright yellow body in breeding males; olive-yellow or duller in females and non-breeding males; white underparts
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black forehead and crown in breeding males; plain face with subtle eye ring in females
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with prominent white wing bars
-Tail Shape and Color: Notched black tail with white edges
-Beak: Short, conical, pinkish-orange
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to light brown legs and feet

European Goldfinch:  
-Size and Shape: Small, slim body with a relatively short neck and tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Warm brown back and flanks, white belly and rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Bright red face mask covering forehead and around eyes, white cheeks, black crown and nape  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with prominent bright yellow wing bars and white spots  
-Tail Shape and Color: Notched tail, black with white tips  
-Beak: Conical, pale ivory, slender and pointed  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish legs and feet, slender

Boat-tailed Grackle:  
-Size and Shape: Large passerine, long tail, slender body  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Males glossy black with iridescent blue-green sheen; females brownish with streaked underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Male head all black and glossy; female with plain brown crown and faint streaking on cheeks  
-Wing Pattern: Uniformly dark in males; females with lighter brown wings, no distinct markings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Very long, keel-shaped tail in males, glossy black; shorter, rounded tail in females, brown  
-Beak: Long, slender, slightly curved, black in males; dark brown in females  
-Legs and Feet: Long, black legs and feet

Eared Grebe:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body; short neck; rounded head  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Slate-gray back; white to pale gray belly and breast; rusty brown flanks in breeding plumage  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Glossy black crown; striking yellow-gold elongated ear tufts extending from behind the eyes; red eyes; dark cheeks and throat  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform dark gray to blackish upper wings with subtle lighter edges  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square tail; dark gray to black  
-Beak: Short, straight, slender; black with pale base  
-Legs and Feet: Legs set far back on body; black feet with lobed toes

Horned Grebe:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body with a short neck and rounded head  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Dark slate-gray to black back; white underparts; rusty or chestnut flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Distinctive golden "horns" formed by tufts of yellow feathers behind deep red eyes; black crown and cheeks; rufous neck and sides of head  
-Wing Pattern: Dark upper wings with lighter underwings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, rounded, dark tail  
-Beak: Short, straight, pointed, black with a pale or whitish base  
-Legs and Feet: Legs set far back on body, dark gray to black, lobed toes

Pied-billed Grebe:
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body; short neck; rounded head; stout profile
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Brownish-gray upperparts; lighter grayish-buff underparts; subtle mottling on flanks; pale rump
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Brown crown and nape; dark stripe through eye; pale throat and cheek
-Wing Pattern: Uniform brownish-gray with no distinct markings
-Tail Shape and Color: Very short, nearly invisible tail; dark brown
-Beak: Thick, pale bill with distinct broad black band around middle (most distinctive feature)
-Legs and Feet: Rear-placed legs; lobed toes; dull gray to greenish legs and feet

Western Grebe:  
-Size and Shape: Large, elongated body; long neck; slender profile  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Dark gray to black back; white breast and belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black crown and nape; bright red eyes; white cheek patch extending to throat, sharply contrasting with black head  
-Wing Pattern: Grayish wings with no distinct markings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square tail; dark gray to black  
-Beak: Long, straight, slender, pale yellow to greenish-yellow  
-Legs and Feet: Positioned far back on body; greenish-gray legs and feet with lobed toes

Blue Grosbeak:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, robust body with thick neck and large head  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Deep cobalt blue overall with rusty wing bars and dark streaks on flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Uniform blue crown, faintly darker blue eyebrow line, no distinct eye ring  
-Wing Pattern: Two prominent chestnut-rusty wing bars on contrasting dark blue wings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Broad, slightly notched tail, blue with subtle darker edges  
-Beak: Large, thick, conical, dark gray to black  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black, sturdy legs and feet

Evening Grosbeak:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-large, chunky body, thick neck, short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Yellow breast and belly, olive-green to gray back and rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Large yellow forehead patch, dark crown and nape, broad white cheek patch  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with prominent white wing patches (secondary coverts and primaries)  
-Tail Shape and Color: Black, slightly notched tail with white edges  
-Beak: Very thick, short, conical, bright yellow to yellow-orange  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black, strong and sturdy

Pine Grosbeak:  
-Size and Shape: Large, chunky finch; thick body, short neck  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Males—rose-red head, breast, and rump; gray back and wings; females and juveniles—yellowish to olive instead of red  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Rounded crown; no strong eye stripe; subtle pale eye ring; cheeks matching overall head color  
-Wing Pattern: Gray wings with two distinct white wing bars; some white patches on flight feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium length, slightly notched tail; gray with faint white edges  
-Beak: Short, thick, conical, and dark gray to black  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black, stout feet and legs

Rose-breasted Grosbeak:
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, robust body with a thick neck and strong build
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Males have black back and wings, bright white underparts, large rose-red triangular patch on breast; females are brown-streaked with buffy underparts
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Males have black crown and nape, white cheek patches; females have streaked brown crown and nape, buffy eyebrow stripe
-Wing Pattern: Large white wing patches on black wings, visible in flight
-Tail Shape and Color: Broad, slightly rounded tail, black with white edges
-Beak: Large, stout, conical, pale pinkish or ivory-colored
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to gray legs and feet, strong for perching

Pigeon Guillemot:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, chunky seabird with a rounded body and relatively short neck  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Glossy black back and upperparts, white belly and underwings  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black head with a small red eye-ring  
-Wing Pattern: Distinctive large white wing patches on black wings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, squared tail, black  
-Beak: Thin, straight, black beak  
-Legs and Feet: Bright red legs and webbed feet

California Gull:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky gull with relatively long wings and moderately rounded tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Light gray back and wings, white breast and belly, white rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White head during non-breeding season with faint smudged grayish markings around eyes; breeding season has clean white head  
-Wing Pattern: Dark gray primary feathers with conspicuous white "mirrors" near wing tips; black tips on primaries  
-Tail Shape and Color: Square to slightly rounded, mostly white tail with narrow gray band near tip (subtle)  
-Beak: Yellow with distinct black subterminal ring and red spot near tip on lower mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Yellow legs and feet

Glaucous-winged Gull:  
-Size and Shape: Large, bulky body with thick neck and broad wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Pale gray back and upper wings, white underparts and head  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Clean white head with pale yellow eyes, faint grayish smudge behind eye, no strong markings  
-Wing Pattern: Pale gray wings with distinctive pale, almost white, wingtips lacking black markings; black primary tips absent  
-Tail Shape and Color: Rounded tail, pale gray matching wings  
-Beak: Thick, yellow with red spot on lower mandible near tip  
-Legs and Feet: Pink legs and feet

Heermann Gull:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized with robust body and relatively short wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Slate gray back and wings, white breast and belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Adult non-breeding has white head; breeding adults have dark gray head; distinct red eye ring  
-Wing Pattern: Dark gray primaries with white trailing edge and black tips  
-Tail Shape and Color: White tail, square-shaped with slight notch  
-Beak: Thick, bright red with black tip  
-Legs and Feet: Bright red legs and feet

Herring Gull:  
-Size and Shape: Large, robust body with broad wings and stout neck  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Light gray back and wings; white breast, belly, and head; pale gray rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White head and neck; pale yellow eye with red orbital ring; pinkish flesh-colored legs  
-Wing Pattern: Gray upper wings with black primary tips featuring distinct white “mirrors” (spots)  
-Tail Shape and Color: White tail with light gray upper tail coverts; slightly rounded tail  
-Beak: Thick, yellow with a prominent red spot on the lower mandible near the tip  
-Legs and Feet: Pink legs and feet, relatively sturdy and webbed

Ivory Gull:
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized gull, stout body, relatively short wings and tail
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Uniformly pure white body and underparts
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): All white head with no distinct markings, dark eyes
-Wing Pattern: White upper wings with subtle pale gray to silvery-gray primary feathers visible in flight
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, squared tail, pure white
-Beak: Short, thick, pale ivory-yellow with a slight dark tip
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black legs and feet

Ring-billed Gull:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky gull with relatively short wings and tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Clean white head, breast, and underparts; light gray back and upper wings  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White head with faint smudged gray around eyes in winter; clear dark ring around the pale yellow eye  
-Wing Pattern: Gray upper wings with black primary tips marked by white "mirrors" at wing tips  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, rounded white tail with faint gray shading near base  
-Beak: Yellow with distinct black ring around the middle (hence the name)  
-Legs and Feet: Greenish-yellow legs and webbed feet

Slaty-backed Gull:
-Size and Shape: Large gull, bulky body, thick neck, robust build
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Dark slate-gray back and wings, white underparts, clean white rump
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White head with faint grayish smudging in non-breeding; yellow eyes with red orbital ring
-Wing Pattern: Dark gray upperwings with contrasting white primary tips and black tail band visible in flight
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, broad tail, white with narrow black band at tip
-Beak: Thick, yellow with red and black markings near tip
-Legs and Feet: Pink legs and feet, sturdy and webbed

Western Gull:  
-Size and Shape: Large, robust body with broad wings and thick neck  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): White head, breast, and belly; medium gray back and upper wings  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Clean white head with yellow eyes; bright red spot on lower mandible of beak  
-Wing Pattern: Gray upper wings with black tips containing white spots ("mirrors")  
-Tail Shape and Color: White tail with faint gray shading underneath  
-Beak: Thick, stout yellow beak with red subterminal spot on lower mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Medium pink legs and webbed feet

Anna Hummingbird:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact with a slightly curved bill  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Metallic green back and sides, lighter grayish-white underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Males with iridescent rose-red crown and gorget, females with green crown and whitish throat  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with subtle green highlights  
-Tail Shape and Color: Slightly forked tail, dark with white tips on outer feathers  
-Beak: Long, slender, straight, black  
-Legs and Feet: Small, black feet

Ruby-throated Hummingbird:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body with rapid wingbeats, slender and slightly curved bill  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Iridescent emerald green back, white to pale underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Glossy emerald green crown and nape, white spot behind the eye  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings, no distinctive markings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Forked tail, dark with white tips on outer feathers  
-Beak: Long, thin, slightly decurved, black  
-Legs and Feet: Tiny, black legs and feet

Rufous Hummingbird:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body with slightly forked tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright rufous (orange-copper) back and flanks; white breast; sometimes greenish back in females  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Males exhibit bright iridescent orange-red throat (gorget); females have speckled throat and greenish crown; no distinct eye ring  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings contrasting with rufous body sides  
-Tail Shape and Color: Tail moderately long, rufous with dark tips, especially on outer feathers  
-Beak: Long, straight, slender, black  
-Legs and Feet: Small, black legs and feet

Green Violetear:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized hummingbird, slender body, slightly curved wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Iridescent green back and breast; bluish-green belly; rufous or bronze rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Metallic green crown; bright violet patch on sides of neck (ear patch); minimal facial markings  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with slight green gloss  
-Tail Shape and Color: Broad, slightly forked tail with dark green and blue iridescence  
-Beak: Long, straight, slender, black  
-Legs and Feet: Small, dark, typical hummingbird feet

Long-tailed Jaeger:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized skua, slender body, very long pointed tail streamers  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Grayish-brown back and wings, paler underparts with variable creamy or white breast and belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Dark crown with contrasting pale supercilium, dark eye stripe through the eye, pale cheek patch  
-Wing Pattern: Long, pointed wings with dark primary tips, subtle pale patches near the base of primaries  
-Tail Shape and Color: Extremely long, slender central tail feathers, grayish with darker tips  
-Beak: Medium length, slender, dark-colored, slightly hooked tip  
-Legs and Feet: Dark legs and feet, webbed

Pomarine Jaeger:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-large seabird, bulky body, broad wings, distinctive thick neck  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Variable plumage; back and wings dark brown to gray, breast and belly pale to buff with streaking or spotting, rump usually lighter  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Crown often darker with pale supercilium, strong dark eye stripe from bill through eye, contrasting cheek patch, nape sometimes with pale collar  
-Wing Pattern: Dark primary wing tips with noticeable paler secondary wing edges, often shows white flash on primaries during flight  
-Tail Shape and Color: Distinctive spoon-shaped central tail feathers, long and broad with pointed tips, dark brown to black coloration  
-Beak: Short, robust, dark with a hooked tip  
-Legs and Feet: Webbed, dark gray to black legs and feet

Blue Jay:
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, robust body with rounded wings
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright blue back and wings, white breast and belly, subtle grayish flanks and rump
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Prominent blue crest on crown, white face with a distinctive black necklace-like band around neck, black eye line extending from bill through eye
-Wing Pattern: Bright blue wings with bold black barring and white patches
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, rounded tail with blue and black bands and white tips
-Beak: Short, stout, black beak
-Legs and Feet: Black, strong legs and feet

Florida Jay:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized passerine, robust body, relatively long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright blue upperparts including back and rump; white or pale underparts with slight buff or pale yellow wash on belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Blue crown and nape; distinct pale face with bold black eyeline extending through eye; white throat patch  
-Wing Pattern: Bright blue wings with possible subtle darker blue or black edging on flight feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, straight tail, bright blue matching back, slightly rounded tip  
-Beak: Medium length, stout, black beak with slight curve  
-Legs and Feet: Strong, black legs and feet

Green Jay:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized passerine with robust body and long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Vibrant green back and wings, bright yellow underparts, blue rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black crown and nape, bright blue facial patch around eyes, white throat patch  
-Wing Pattern: Green wings with subtle blue edges  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long tail, blue with green undertones  
-Beak: Short, stout, black beak  
-Legs and Feet: Grayish legs and feet

Dark-eyed Junco:  
-Size and Shape: Small, plump body; short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Slate-gray back and head; white belly and undertail coverts; pale pinkish flank wash  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Uniform slate-gray crown and nape; no eye ring or distinct markings  
-Wing Pattern: Dark gray wings with two faint white wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, notched tail; outer tail feathers white contrasting with dark central tail feathers  
-Beak: Small, conical, pale pink to flesh-colored  
-Legs and Feet: Fine, pale pinkish legs and feet

Tropical Kingbird:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, robust body; broad, rounded wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-gray back; bright yellow underparts (breast, belly); pale rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Grayish head and crown; distinct pale yellowish-white throat; faint eye-ring  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with narrow pale wing bars (from feather edges)  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, squared tail with white outer edges  
-Beak: Medium-length, broad, blackish beak with slightly hooked tip  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black, sturdy legs and feet

Gray Kingbird:
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, robust body; long wings; moderately long tail
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Light gray upperparts, whitish to pale gray underparts
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Gray crown and nape; distinct dark eye-line extending from bill through eye; pale throat
-Wing Pattern: Dark gray wings with faint wingbars not prominent
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, squared tail with dark gray color and narrow white terminal band
-Beak: Stout, blackish, slightly hooked upper mandible
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black legs and feet

Belted Kingfisher:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized; stocky body; large head; short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Slate blue back and wings; white underparts with a broad blue band across the breast; females have an additional rusty band on the belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Large shaggy crest; white collar around the neck; slate blue crown and nape; dark eye stripe extending from bill through eye to nape  
-Wing Pattern: Blue with faint white spotting visible in flight  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium length, squared tail; blue with white barring  
-Beak: Long, straight, black, and robust  
-Legs and Feet: Short, dark gray to black legs and feet

Green Kingfisher:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body with short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright green upperparts; white throat and breast; rusty or rufous flanks and belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Green crown with fine white spots; distinct white collar around neck; dark line through eye; white spots on cheek and nape  
-Wing Pattern: Green wings with small white spotting  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square tail; green with faint barring  
-Beak: Short, straight, and pointed; black upper mandible; slightly lighter lower mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Small, orange-red legs and feet

Pied Kingfisher:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky, with a relatively short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Black-and-white patterned back; white underparts with black breast band and additional faint breast spotting  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Prominent black crest on crown; bold black eye stripe extending from bill through eye to nape; white cheeks and throat  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with distinct white patches and spots  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, black tail with white edges and central white spots  
-Beak: Straight, long, sharp, black bill  
-Legs and Feet: Short, black legs and feet

Ringed Kingfisher:  
-Size and Shape: Large, robust body with thick neck and long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Slate blue back and wings; white underparts with broad rusty chest band  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Large blue-gray crest; white collar around neck; prominent dark eye stripe  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform slate blue upper wings with subtle darker edges  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, squared tail with blue and black barring  
-Beak: Large, straight, thick, dark gray to black  
-Legs and Feet: Short, strong, reddish legs and feet

White-breasted Kingfisher:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky body with large head and short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright turquoise to blue back and wings, white breast and belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Brownish head and nape, white throat and collar around neck  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform bright blue wings with no distinct markings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square tail, bright blue matching wings  
-Beak: Large, stout, bright red to orange-red beak, slightly hooked tip  
-Legs and Feet: Red to orange legs and feet, relatively short and strong

Red-legged Kittiwake:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized gull, stocky with relatively short wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Pale gray back and upper wings, white breast and belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White head with a distinctive dark gray smudge behind and below the eye  
-Wing Pattern: Black primary tips with a white "mirrored" spot on the outer primaries  
-Tail Shape and Color: White tail with narrow black band near the tip  
-Beak: Short, slender, bright red or orange-red beak  
-Legs and Feet: Bright red legs and feet, webbed

Horned Lark:  
-Size and Shape: Small, slender body with a relatively long tail and short wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Warm tan to light brown back, pale cream to white underparts, slightly buffy flanks, and yellowish rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Distinctive black "horns" (feather tufts), black facial mask extending through eyes, bright yellow throat and face patch, white supercilium (eyebrow line), black cheek patches, and a white nape collar  
-Wing Pattern: Brown wings with subtle darker streaks  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, pointed tail with white outer tail feathers  
-Beak: Short, slender, pale pinkish to light horn-colored  
-Legs and Feet: Pale brown to flesh-colored legs and feet

Pacific Loon:  
-Size and Shape: Medium to large, streamlined body; moderately long neck  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Back and wings blackish with dense white spots; breast and belly white  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Dark gray to black head and neck with slight greenish gloss; striking white vertical stripes on neck sides  
-Wing Pattern: Blackish wings with scattered white spots on upper surface  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, rounded, dark gray to black tail  
-Beak: Straight, pointed, medium length, gray to black  
-Legs and Feet: Positioned far back on body; dark gray to black webbed feet

Mallard:
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized duck, broad body, relatively short neck
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Males have iridescent green back on neck extending to head, chestnut-brown breast, pale gray flanks, white-bordered blue speculum on wings
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Males exhibit iridescent green head, white neck ring, yellow bill; females have mottled brown head with dark eye stripe
-Wing Pattern: Prominent blue speculum edged with white bands on secondary feathers
-Tail Shape and Color: Slightly upturned tail with black central feathers and white outer feathers in males; mottled brown in females
-Beak: Males have smooth yellow bill; females' bill is orange with dark splotches
-Legs and Feet: Orange legs and webbed feet

Western Meadowlark:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky songbird with a slightly rounded body and long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright yellow breast and belly with a distinctive black "V" shaped bib; mottled brown and buff streaked back and flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Chestnut brown crown with faint streaking; bold white and black stripes on face with a white supercilium above eye  
-Wing Pattern: Brown wings with buffy wing bars and fine streaking  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, pointed tail with white outer tail feathers visible in flight  
-Beak: Long, slender, slightly curved and pointed; pale grayish to brownish color  
-Legs and Feet: Strong, pale brown legs and feet adapted for ground foraging

Hooded Merganser:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized duck, slender body, narrow neck, prominent fan-shaped crest  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Males have dark back, white breast with chestnut flanks; females are grayish-brown overall  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Male with large white patch on black crest; female with brown crest and white throat patch  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with white secondary patches visible in flight  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square tail, dark brown to black  
-Beak: Thin, serrated, dark gray to black, slightly hooked tip  
-Legs and Feet: Orange to reddish-orange, webbed feet

Red-breasted Merganser:
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slender diving duck; thin neck; spiky crest on head
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Dark gray to black back; rusty reddish breast; white belly; mottled gray flanks; white patch on rump
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Dark greenish-black crown with shaggy crest; sharp red eye; white neck ring; rusty-brown neck sides and cheeks
-Wing Pattern: Blackish wings with a distinct white patch visible in flight
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium length, pointed tail, dark gray to black
-Beak: Long, narrow, serrated bright red-orange bill, slightly hooked tip
-Legs and Feet: Short, reddish legs with webbed feet

Mockingbird:
-Size and Shape: Medium size, slender body, long legs and neck
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Grayish upperparts, white underparts with slight buff on flanks
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Plain gray crown, distinct white eye line above eye, no crest
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with two prominent white wing bars and white patches visible in flight
-Tail Shape and Color: Long tail with white outer tail feathers visible in flight
-Beak: Thin, slightly curved, dark gray or black
-Legs and Feet: Long, slender, dark gray to black legs and feet

Nighthawk:  
-Size and Shape: Medium size, slim body, long pointed wings with a distinctive boomerang shape  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Mottled brown, gray, and white camouflage pattern; breast and belly lighter with irregular dark bars  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Small head, dark crown with subtle white or light marks near eyes, white throat patch prominent  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with a broad white or pale bar across the primaries visible in flight  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, slightly notched tail with white or light band near the tip  
-Beak: Very short, slightly hooked, dark  
-Legs and Feet: Small, weak, grayish legs and feet

Clark Nutcracker:
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, robust body with a strong, slightly curved bill
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Light gray body with white underparts, subtle buffy wash on flanks
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Gray crown and nape, dark eye with no distinct eye ring or stripe
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with distinct white patches visible in flight
-Tail Shape and Color: Long black tail with white outer feathers
-Beak: Long, straight, black, robust and pointed
-Legs and Feet: Black legs and feet, strong and sturdy

White-breasted Nuthatch:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body; short tail; strong posture  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Slate blue-gray back; white breast and belly; buffy or light tawny flanks; white rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black crown and nape; prominent white face and throat; black eye line extending from bill past eye  
-Wing Pattern: Slate blue-gray wings with subtle blackish flight feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square tail; blue-gray with blackish tips  
-Beak: Straight, slender, slightly upturned; grayish-black  
-Legs and Feet: Grayish legs and feet; strong toes with sharp claws for climbing bark

Baltimore Oriole:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slender body with a slightly pointed tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright orange breast and belly; black back and upperparts; white patch on lower rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black head and throat; sharp contrast with orange face and chest  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with two distinct white wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, slightly forked tail; predominantly black with orange edges  
-Beak: Straight, slender, pointed; pale gray to light brown  
-Legs and Feet: Pale gray to pinkish legs and feet

Hooded Oriole:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slender body with long tail and pointed wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright orange to yellow-orange body with black back and wings  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black hood covering crown and nape extending to upper back; sharp contrast with orange face and throat  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with faint yellowish edges on feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, pointed tail feathers, mostly orange with some black near base  
-Beak: Long, slender, slightly curved downward, blackish coloration  
-Legs and Feet: Grayish legs and feet, thin and delicate structure

Orchard Oriole:  
-Size and Shape: Small, slender, pointed wings and slightly curved tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Male black back and wings; chestnut to rich orange breast and belly; female olive-green back and yellow-orange underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Male glossy black head and throat; female olive-green crown and nape with no distinct eye markings  
-Wing Pattern: Male black wings with white wing bars; female wings dull olive with faint pale wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, slightly notched tail; male black, female olive-green  
-Beak: Short, sharp, pointed, pale horn to grayish  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black, slender legs and feet

Scott Oriole:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, slender passerine; medium-length tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright orange-yellow underparts; black back and upperparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black head including crown and nape; no distinct eye ring or facial markings  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with bold white wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Black tail, slightly rounded  
-Beak: Medium-length, pointed, slightly curved downward, black  
-Legs and Feet: Dark gray to black legs and feet

Ovenbird:  
-Size and Shape: Small, chunky warbler with rounded body and relatively short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-brown upperparts; white breast and belly heavily streaked with black on breast and flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Olive crown with a distinct broken white eye ring; prominent dark line through the eye; buffy or orange eyebrow stripe; pale cheeks  
-Wing Pattern: Plain olive-brown wings with subtle wingbars rarely visible  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, rounded tail, olive-brown matching back  
-Beak: Short, slender, slightly pointed, pale pinkish or flesh-toned with darker tip  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish legs and feet, fairly long for body size

Brown Pelican:  
-Size and Shape: Large body, long neck, bulky with a distinctive pouch under the beak  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Brown-gray back and wings, white or pale yellow breast, lighter belly, rusty brown flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White or pale yellow crown and nape, dark eye stripe extending from eye to throat pouch, pale face  
-Wing Pattern: Broad wings with dark brown primary feathers contrasting lighter secondary feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square tail, brownish-gray  
-Beak: Very long, straight, pale gray with a darker hooked tip, large throat pouch underneath  
-Legs and Feet: Short, webbed feet, gray to brownish color

White Pelican:  
-Size and Shape: Very large, bulky body with long neck and broad wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Mostly bright white plumage throughout body  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White head with slight yellowish tint near crown, pale orange skin around eyes  
-Wing Pattern: Black primary and secondary flight feathers contrasted against white smaller coverts  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, square-shaped white tail  
-Beak: Very long, thick bright orange bill with large, expandable throat pouch  
-Legs and Feet: Short, sturdy legs and large webbed feet, pale orange to pinkish color

Western Wood Pewee:
-Size and Shape: Small, slender flycatcher with a narrow body and long wings
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-gray upperparts; pale yellowish to whitish underparts with faint wash on breast
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Slightly crested crown; faint, thin pale eye-ring; subtle darker line through the eye; nape similar to back color
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with two thin, pale wing bars
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, slightly rounded dark tail with faint pale edges
-Beak: Small, blackish upper mandible; paler lower mandible
-Legs and Feet: Dark, slender legs and feet

Sayornis (e.g., Eastern Phoebe, Say's Phoebe):
-Size and Shape: Medium small, slender flycatcher with relatively long tail and upright posture
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-brown to grayish-brown upperparts; pale off-white to buffy underparts with subtle wash on breast
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Plain head; slight darker cap on some species; faint or no distinct eye ring or cheek patch
-Wing Pattern: Wings darker than back with faint wing bars or none; subtle dusky edges on wing feathers
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, rounded tail; dark with paler edges or base depending on species
-Beak: Short, thin, and pointed; dark upper mandible and paler lower mandible
-Legs and Feet: Thin, dark legs and feet adapted for perching

American Pipit:  
-Size and Shape: Small, slender songbird with medium-length tail and relatively long legs  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Brownish-olive back with faint streaking; buffy breast with fine dark streaks; pale belly; light rusty or buffy flanks; white rump visible in flight  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Brown crown with subtle streaks; distinct pale supercilium (eyebrow line); dark line through eye; buffy cheeks; nape streaked with brown  
-Wing Pattern: Brown wings with faint wingbars (often two pale bars); subtle darker flight feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length tail with white outer tail feathers contrasting brown central feathers  
-Beak: Thin, slender, dark with slightly paler base  
-Legs and Feet: Long, slender, dark legs and feet

Whip-poor-will:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, plump body; short neck; long, rounded wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Mottled gray, brown, black on back and wings; pale gray to buff breast and belly with fine streaks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Cryptic mottled crown; distinct white throat patch; dark eyes with subtle buffy eyebrow line  
-Wing Pattern: Mottled with light and dark patches; prominent white wing patches visible in flight  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, rounded tail with alternating dark and light bands and white tips on outer tail feathers  
-Beak: Short, broad, slightly curved, dark in color  
-Legs and Feet: Short, grayish legs and feet with small toes

Horned Puffin:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky seabird with compact body  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Black back and upper wings, white breast and belly  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White face with distinct small fleshy "horns" above eyes during breeding season; bright orange-yellow patch at base of bill  
-Wing Pattern: Solid black upper wings with no distinct markings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, rounded, black tail  
-Beak: Large, triangular, brightly colored with orange, yellow, and gray vertical grooves, prominent red gape line  
-Legs and Feet: Bright orange, webbed feet

Common Raven:
-Size and Shape: Large, heavy body; thick neck; wedge-shaped tail
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Uniform glossy black with iridescent blue-purple sheen
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Shaggy throat feathers; robust head with no distinctive markings
-Wing Pattern: Long, broad wings with slightly ragged primary feathers
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, wedge-shaped tail, solid black
-Beak: Large, thick, curved black beak with slight hook at tip
-Legs and Feet: Strong, black legs and feet with sturdy toes

White-necked Raven:  
-Size and Shape: Large, robust body with thick neck and strong build  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Glossy black body with slight iridescence  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Distinct white patch of feathers on the nape (back of the neck) contrasting with black head and crown; dark eyes  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform glossy black wings with subtle iridescent sheen; no contrasting markings  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, wedge-shaped, uniformly black tail  
-Beak: Large, thick, black bill slightly curved downward at tip  
-Legs and Feet: Strong, black legs and feet with robust claws

American Redstart:
-Size and Shape: Small, slim songbird with a relatively long tail

-Tail Shape and Color: Long, fan-shaped tail with bright orange (males) or yellow (females) outer tail feathers
-Beak: Small, thin, straight, dark gray to black
-Legs and Feet: Thin, dark gray legs and feet

Geococcyx (Greater Roadrunner):  
-Size and Shape: Medium-large, elongated body with long legs and tail

-Tail Shape and Color: Long, graduated tail with dark brown feathers tipped with white  
-Beak: Long, straight, slightly curved downward, dark gray to black  
-Legs and Feet: Long legs, strong feet with two toes facing forward and two backward (zygodactyl arrangement)

Loggerhead Shrike:

-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Gray back and upperparts, white underparts with pale buff on flanks and undertail coverts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black mask extending through eyes, gray crown and nape, white throat  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with distinct white patches visible in flight  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, squared tail with white edges  
-Beak: Short, strong, hooked beak, predominantly black  
-Legs and Feet: Black legs and feet, medium length

Great Grey Shrike:

-Tail Shape and Color: Long, square-tipped tail; black with white outer feathers  
-Beak: Strong, black, slightly hooked at tip  
-Legs and Feet: Black, strong legs and feet

Baird's Sparrow:

-Tail Shape and Color: Short, slightly rounded tail; brown with some faint darker barring

Black-throated Sparrow:

-Tail Shape and Color: Medium length, notched tail with brown and gray tones  
-Beak: Small, conical, pale horn to grayish color  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to flesh-colored legs and feet

Brewer Sparrow:  
-Size and Shape: Small, slim sparrow with a relatively short tail

-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, slightly notched tail, brown with faint dusky edges

-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to light brown legs and feet

Chipping Sparrow:

-Beak: Short, slender, conical, pinkish with darker tip
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to flesh-colored legs and feet

Clay-colored Sparrow:

-Tail Shape and Color: Short, slightly notched tail, brown coloration  
-Beak: Small, conical, pale pinkish to horn-colored  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to flesh-colored legs and feet

House Sparrow:

Field Sparrow:

-Tail Shape and Color: Short, notched tail with rufous coloring  
-Beak: Pinkish, conical beak  
-Legs and Feet: Pink legs and feet

Fox Sparrow:

-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, rounded tail; rufous-brown color matching back

-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to brown legs and feet, strong and sturdy

Grasshopper Sparrow:

-Tail Shape and Color: Short, notched tail; tail feathers brown with variable pale edges  
-Beak: Short, conical, pinkish or horn-colored beak  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish or flesh-colored legs and feet

Harris Sparrow:

-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length tail, brown with faint edges

Henslow's Sparrow:

-Tail Shape and Color: Short, rounded tail with brown and gray tones

-Legs and Feet: Pale pink to light brown legs and feet

Le Conte Sparrow:

-Tail Shape and Color: Short, slightly notched tail, warm brown with faint darker streaks  
-Beak: Small, conical, pale pinkish or horn-colored bill  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to flesh-colored legs and feet

Lincoln Sparrow:
-Size and Shape: Small, plump, short-tailed sparrow

-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, notched tail, brown with faint edges
-Beak: Small, pinkish with darker tip, conical shape
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish-brown legs and feet

Nelson's Sharp-tailed Sparrow:

-Tail Shape and Color: Long, narrow, sharply pointed tail; brown with black streaking
-Beak: Short, conical, pinkish to pale yellowish base with darker tip
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to pale brown legs and feet

Savannah Sparrow:

-Tail Shape and Color: Slightly notched, brown tail with subtle white edges  
-Beak: Short, conical, pinkish or horn-colored with darker tip  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to flesh-colored legs and feet

Seaside Sparrow:

-Legs and Feet: Flesh-colored to pale gray legs and feet

Song Sparrow:

Tree Sparrow:

Vesper Sparrow:

-Legs and Feet: Long pale pinkish legs and feet

White-crowned Sparrow:
