Swainson's Warbler:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-small, robust body, fairly long tail, short wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Rich warm brown back and upperparts, buffy to pale reddish-brown underparts, slightly lighter belly, faintly streaked flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Uniform warm brown crown, distinct pale supercilium (eyebrow line), rusty cheek patch, plain nape matching back  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform warm brown wings without prominent wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Rounded, warm brown tail, slightly darker than back  
-Beak: Relatively long, straight, pale pinkish or horn-colored beak  
-Legs and Feet: Pale, pinkish legs and feet

Tennessee Warbler:  
-Size and Shape: Small, slender body with short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-green back, white to pale yellow underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Gray crown, distinct white eye ring, faint eye stripe, pale cheeks  
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with two white wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, slightly notched tail, olive-green  
-Beak: Thin, pointed, dark gray  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to gray legs and feet

Wilson Warbler:
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body with a rounded head and short tail
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright yellow underparts, olive-green to yellowish back
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Distinct black cap on crown, bright yellow face without eye ring, slightly darker cheek patch
-Wing Pattern: Olive-green wings with faint wing bars rarely visible
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, slightly rounded tail, olive-green matching back
-Beak: Short, slender, pointed, dark gray to black
-Legs and Feet: Thin, dark gray to black legs and feet

Worm-eating Warbler:
-Size and Shape: Small, slender body; rounded tail; short neck
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-brown back; pale yellowish breast and belly with fine streaking on sides
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Distinctive black crown stripes separated by a broad yellow central crown stripe; bold black eye stripe through eye; white supercilium; pale yellow throat; buffy cheeks
-Wing Pattern: Olive-brown wings with faint wing bars
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, rounded tail, olive-brown
-Beak: Thin, slightly downcurved, dark upper mandible, paler lower mandible
-Legs and Feet: Pale pinkish legs and feet

Yellow Warbler:  
-Size and Shape: Small, slender, slightly rounded body; short wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Bright yellow overall; breast and belly yellow with distinct rusty red streaks on breast and flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Uniform yellow crown; no distinct eye ring or stripe; subtle olive wash on nape  
-Wing Pattern: Yellow wings with faint olive-green edging; no bold wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, slightly forked tail; yellow with faint olive edges  
-Beak: Thin, pointed, pale pinkish or grayish  
-Legs and Feet: Slender, pale pink or flesh-colored legs and feet

Northern Waterthrush:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-small, stocky warbler with relatively long tail, slightly rounded wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-brown upperparts, heavily streaked buffy-white breast and throat, pale belly, faintly buffy flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Bold white supercilium extending from base of bill backward, dark brown crown with faint streaks, dark stripe through eye, pale cheek  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform olive-brown wings with faint wing bars or none  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium length, narrow tail, brown with faint edges  
-Beak: Thin, slightly curved, dark with paler base on lower mandible  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to brownish legs and feet, relatively long toes

Louisiana Waterthrush:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky warbler with a relatively long tail and strong legs  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Brown upperparts; white underparts heavily streaked with dark brown on breast and flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Bold white supercilium extending past eye; dark crown with subtle streaking; dark line through the eye  
-Wing Pattern: Brown wings with faint pale wing bars or streaks  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium-length, rounded tail, brown matching back coloration  
-Beak: Thin, slightly curved, pinkish or grayish base with darker tip  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish to grayish legs, relatively long and strong for wading

Bohemian Waxwing:  
-Size and Shape: Medium, plump crest on head, compact body  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Soft gray-brown body, pale yellow undertail, rusty undertail coverts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Prominent pointed crest, black mask through eye, white line above mask, rusty brown crown and nape  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with bright yellow and white wing bars, red waxy tips on secondary feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Square tail with bright yellow terminal band  
-Beak: Short, black, slightly hooked tip  
-Legs and Feet: Black legs and feet, slender toes

Cedar Waxwing:  
-Size and Shape: Medium, sleek body with a prominent crest on head  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Soft brown to tan head and chest, pale gray wings and back, yellow belly, bright yellow terminal tail band  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black mask bordered with white lines, cinnamon-buff throat, crest on crown  
-Wing Pattern: Gray wings with small, bright red waxy tips on secondary feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Square tail with bright yellow band at tip  
-Beak: Short, black, slightly hooked  
-Legs and Feet: Short, black legs and feet

American Three-toed Woodpecker:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, compact woodpecker; sturdy body with relatively short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Black upperparts with white barred or spotted pattern on back; pale yellowish to creamy underparts with faint streaking  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Males have yellow crown patch; both sexes have white face with black line through eye and black cheek patch; nape black  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with white spots and slightly barred secondary coverts  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, stiff tail feathers; black with white outer edges  
-Beak: Straight, chisel-like, medium-length, grayish to black  
-Legs and Feet: Gray to dark gray legs; three toes (lacking the usual fourth hind toe)

Pileated Woodpecker:
-Size and Shape: Large woodpecker, approximately crow-sized, with a strong, chisel-like bill
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Mostly black body with white underwings visible in flight; white stripes on neck
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Prominent red crest on crown; white line from bill to neck; black face with red malar stripe in males (absent in females)
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with white underwing linings visible in flight
-Tail Shape and Color: Stiff, black tail feathers, used for support on tree trunks
-Beak: Long, powerful, straight, pale gray to ivory colored
-Legs and Feet: Strong, gray legs with zygodactyl feet (two toes forward, two back) for gripping vertical surfaces

Red-bellied Woodpecker:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized woodpecker, sturdy body, moderately long tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Pale grayish face and underparts, faint reddish wash on belly, barred black and white back and wings  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Bright red crown and nape extending from bill to upper neck (more extensive in males), pale cheek area  
-Wing Pattern: Black and white horizontal barring across wings and back  
-Tail Shape and Color: Stiff, pointed tail with black central feathers, outer feathers white with black barring  
-Beak: Medium-length, straight, chisel-like, grayish or blackish  
-Legs and Feet: Strong, gray to blue-gray feet with zygodactyl toes (two forward, two backward)

Red-cockaded Woodpecker:  
-Size and Shape: Small woodpecker, slender body, rounded head  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-green to blackish back, white underparts with faint barring on sides  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black cap with small white cheek patch; males show narrow red streak ("cockade") on side of black cap near eye  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with white spotting or streaking on flight feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Stiff tail with black central feathers and white outer edges  
-Beak: Short, chisel-shaped, grayish to blackish  
-Legs and Feet: Gray, strong feet with sharp claws for gripping bark

Red-headed Woodpecker:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stout body; straight posture  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Glossy black back and wings; bright white belly, breast, and rump  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Entire head bright solid red, including crown and nape; no eye markings  
-Wing Pattern: Large white patches on black wings, highly contrasting, visible in flight and at rest  
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium length, black tail with white edges (often less visible)  
-Beak: Straight, chisel-like, medium length, black  
-Legs and Feet: Grayish-black, strong claws for gripping bark

Downy Woodpecker:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body; short neck; relatively short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Black and white checkered back; white underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): White stripe down center of crown; black side of head with white stripe through eye; males have small red patch on back of crown  
-Wing Pattern: Black wings with white spots forming bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short tail with outer feathers white and inner feathers black with white edges  
-Beak: Short, straight, chisel-like, relatively slender and black  
-Legs and Feet: Grayish legs with strong feet and sharp claws for clinging to tree bark

Bewick Wren:  
-Size and Shape: Small, slender body; relatively long tail often held upright  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Warm brown back; pale grayish-white underparts; buffy flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Bold white supercilium extending past the eye; plain grayish-brown crown and nape  
-Wing Pattern: Uniform brown wings with faint barring on flight feathers  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, narrow tail with distinct dark barring on underside and plain brown upper side  
-Beak: Thin, slightly curved, dark gray to black  
-Legs and Feet: Pale pinkish to gray legs and feet

Cactus Wren:  
-Size and Shape: Medium-sized, stocky, with a long tail slightly curved downward  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Brown and buff streaked back, heavily spotted white breast and belly, warm buff flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Prominent white supercilium extending past the eye, spotted crown with brown and white, buffy cheek with dark streaks  
-Wing Pattern: Brown wings with white spots and streaks, noticeable barring  
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, rounded tail with white spots on outer feathers, dark brown base color  
-Beak: Slightly curved, medium-length, thick and blackish-gray  
-Legs and Feet: Strong, grayish legs and feet adapted for climbing in shrubs

Carolina Wren:
-Size and Shape: Small, plump body with a long, slightly cocked tail
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Warm reddish-brown back, pale buffy-white underparts with faint barring on flanks
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Prominent white eyebrow stripe extending from bill to nape, brown crown, pale buff cheeks
-Wing Pattern: Plain reddish-brown wings without wing bars
-Tail Shape and Color: Long, held upright; warm reddish-brown with faint darker barring
-Beak: Thin, slightly curved, grayish to brownish
-Legs and Feet: Pale brown to gray legs and feet

House Wren:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body with short neck and tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Warm brown upperparts with faint darker barring, pale grayish to buffy underparts  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Slightly streaked crown, faint pale supercilium, unmarked cheeks  
-Wing Pattern: Brown wings with subtle barring, no bold wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, rounded tail, brown with faint barring  
-Beak: Thin, slightly curved, dark gray to black  
-Legs and Feet: Medium length, grayish to brown legs and feet

Marsh Wren:
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body with short neck and rounded wings
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Warm brown back with faint dark barring; pale buffy underparts with light streaking on sides and breast
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Prominent white supercilium; dark stripe through eye; rufous-brown crown with subtle streaks
-Wing Pattern: Dark wings with faint barring, edged with paler feather tips
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, frequently cocked upward; dark brown with light barring
-Beak: Thin, slightly decurved, pale horn-colored
-Legs and Feet: Long, slender, pale gray to brownish legs and feet

Rock Wren:
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body; relatively short tail; slender build
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Brownish-gray back with fine dark streaks; pale, buffy underparts with faint streaking on breast; slightly paler rump
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Grayish crown with subtle streaks; prominent whitish supercilium; pale cheeks; nape similar to back but slightly lighter
-Wing Pattern: Brownish wings with faint pale wing bars; subtle mottling
-Tail Shape and Color: Medium length, narrow tail with dark central feathers and buffy edges; often held cocked upwards
-Beak: Thin, slightly curved, medium length, dark to grayish
-Legs and Feet: Long, slender legs and toes; pale gray to pinkish color

Winter Wren:  
-Size and Shape: Very small, compact body with short neck and short tail  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Rich dark brown upperparts with fine pale barring; warm brown underparts with subtle streaks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Prominent pale supercilium, dark eye line, finely streaked crown and nape  
-Wing Pattern: Uniformly brown with faint barring, no distinct wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, often held cocked upwards, barred brown and black  
-Beak: Short, thin, slightly curved, dark brown  
-Legs and Feet: Long, slender legs and toes, pale brown to pinkish

Common Yellowthroat:  
-Size and Shape: Small, compact body with rounded wings  
-Overall Coloration (back, breast, belly, flank, rump...): Olive-green back; bright yellow throat and breast; lighter yellow belly; subtle grayish flanks  
-Head Details (crown, eye markings, cheek, nape...): Black mask across eyes bordered above with bright white or yellowish line; olive crown; yellowish face outside mask  
-Wing Pattern: Olive wings with faint, indistinct wing bars  
-Tail Shape and Color: Short, rounded tail; olive with faint yellowish edges  
-Beak: Short, thin, pointed, dark gray or black  
-Legs and Feet: Pinkish or flesh-colored legs and feet
